.Dd April 25, 2026
.Dt SSHDISPATCHER 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm sshdispatcher
.Nd transparent SSH wrapper that routes legacy DSA-only hosts to plink
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Op Fl p Ar port
.Op Fl l Ar user
.Op Ar options
.Ar [user@]host
.Op Ar command
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
is a thin wrapper around
.Xr ssh 1
designed for managed network equipment (such as TP-Link JetStream switches)
that only supports
.Cm ssh-dss
(DSA 1024-bit) host keys.
DSA was removed from OpenSSH 9.8 and cannot be re-enabled.
.Pp
.Nm
inspects
.Pa ~/.ssh/config
at startup and builds a list of
.Dq legacy
hosts.
For those hosts it delegates to
.Xr plink 1
(the PuTTY command-line client, which retains DSA support).
All other hosts are passed through unchanged to the real
.Xr ssh 1 .
.Sh DETECTION
A host stanza in
.Pa ~/.ssh/config
is classified as legacy when it contains the line:
.Pp
.Dl HostKeyAlgorithms +ssh-dss
.Pp
either live or as a comment:
.Pp
.Dl # HostKeyAlgorithms +ssh-dss
.Pp
The commented form is preferred because it keeps
.Ic ssh -G
working and avoids parse errors in OpenSSH 10+ (which no longer recognises
.Cm ssh-dss
as a valid algorithm token).
All host aliases listed on the
.Ic Host
line of the matching stanza are registered as legacy.
.Sh OPTIONS
.Nm
recognises the same flags as
.Xr ssh 1 .
The flags listed below receive special treatment:
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Fl p Ar port
Passed to
.Xr plink 1
as
.Fl P Ar port .
.It Fl l Ar user
Sets the login user for
.Xr plink 1 .
.El
.Pp
For non-legacy hosts every argument is forwarded verbatim to
.Xr ssh 1 .
For legacy hosts the dispatcher reconstructs a minimal
.Xr plink 1
command line; flags not listed above are not forwarded (plink uses its own
negotiation for ciphers and key exchange).
.Sh IDENTITY FILES
PuTTY uses its own
.Pa .ppk
key format instead of the OpenSSH format.
Conversion is one-time and deliberate:
.Pp
.Dl puttygen ~/.ssh/switch_key -O private -o ~/.ssh/switch_key.ppk
.Pp
When dispatching to
.Xr plink 1 ,
.Nm
resolves the
.Ic IdentityFile
entries from
.Pa ~/.ssh/config
via
.Ic ssh -G .
For each candidate path it checks for a
.Pa .ppk
sibling at the same location.
If found, that file is passed to
.Xr plink 1
as
.Fl i Ar path .ppk .
If multiple candidates have
.Pa .ppk
siblings, the first one wins (matching OpenSSH first-match-wins behaviour).
If no
.Pa .ppk
sibling exists,
.Fl i
is omitted and
.Xr plink 1
falls back to a password prompt.
.Pp
OpenSSH default identity files
.Pq Pa id_rsa , Pa id_ed25519 , etc.
are returned by
.Ic ssh -G
even when not configured explicitly.
The
.Pa .ppk
sibling rule naturally excludes them unless the user has deliberately converted them.
.Sh EXAMPLES
Sample
.Pa ~/.ssh/config
stanza:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
Host switch switch.local 172.17.17.12 switch.fi
    HostName 172.17.17.12
    User admin
    IdentityFile ~/.ssh/switch_key
    # HostKeyAlgorithms +ssh-dss
    KexAlgorithms +diffie-hellman-group1-sha1
    Ciphers aes256-cbc
.Ed
.Pp
All four aliases
.Pq Cm switch , Cm switch.local , Cm 172.17.17.12 , Cm switch.fi
are detected as legacy.
.Pp
Connect to the switch (plink is used transparently):
.Pp
.Dl ssh switch
.Pp
Connect to a normal host (real ssh is used):
.Pp
.Dl ssh user@myserver.example.com
.Pp
Connect on a non-standard port:
.Pp
.Dl ssh -p 2222 switch
.Sh FILES
.Bl -tag -width Pa
.It Pa ~/.ssh/config
Standard OpenSSH configuration file.
Both legacy detection and config resolution
.Pq user, port, IdentityFile
read from this file.
.It Pa /usr/local/bin/sshdispatcher
Default install location (symlink to the repository copy).
.It Pa /usr/local/share/man/man1/sshdispatcher.1
Default man page location (symlink to the repository copy).
.El
.Sh ENVIRONMENT
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Ev SSHDISPATCHER_SSH
Override the path to the real
.Xr ssh 1
binary.
Useful for testing.
.It Ev SSHDISPATCHER_PLINK
Override the path to
.Xr plink 1 .
Set to an empty string to simulate a missing plink.
Useful for testing.
.El
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr ssh 1 ,
.Xr ssh_config 5 ,
.Xr plink 1 ,
.Xr puttygen 1
.Sh LIMITATIONS
.Bl -bullet
.It
Only
.Xr ssh 1
dispatch is implemented.
.Xr scp 1 ,
.Xr sftp 1 ,
and
.Xr rsync 1
over legacy hosts are not handled.
.It
Host-key fingerprint pinning is not implemented.
The
.Fl hostkey No \&*
flag passed to
.Xr plink 1
accepts any host key on first connection.
.It
.Xr plink 1
does not read
.Ic KexAlgorithms
or
.Ic Ciphers
from
.Pa ~/.ssh/config .
It negotiates its own key exchange and cipher suite, which may differ from
what is configured for
.Xr ssh 1 .
.El
